```cpp
#include <hexi/hexi.h>
#include <vector>
#include <string>
#include <cstdint>

struct NetworkPacket {
    uint32_t packet_id;
    std::string username;
    std::vector<uint32_t> scores;
    std::string metadata;

    void serialise(auto& stream) {
        // Write packet_id (POD type, will be written directly)
        stream << packet_id;

        // Write username with length prefix using prefixed adaptor
        stream << hexi::prefixed(username);

        // Write scores vector with count first, then elements using operator<<
        // The operator<< for prefixed containers handles this automatically
        stream << hexi::prefixed(scores);

        // Write metadata as null-terminated string using null_terminated adaptor
        stream << hexi::null_terminated(metadata);
    }
};

std::vector<uint8_t> serialize_packet(const NetworkPacket& packet) {
    // Create a buffer to hold the serialized data
    std::vector<uint8_t> buffer;

    // Create a buffer_adaptor for the buffer
    hexi::buffer_adaptor<std::vector<uint8_t>> adaptor(buffer);

    // Create a binary_stream using the buffer_adaptor
    hexi::binary_stream<decltype(adaptor)> stream(adaptor);

    // Call the serialise method on the packet object with the stream
    packet.serialise(stream);

    // Return the buffer containing the serialized data
    return buffer;
}
```

## Key Implementation Points:

1. **Packet ID Serialization**: Used `stream << packet_id` which automatically handles POD types like `uint32_t`.

2. **Username Serialization**: Used `hexi::prefixed(username)` adaptor which writes the string length as a prefix before the string data.

3. **Scores Vector Serialization**: Used `hexi::prefixed(scores)` which automatically writes the count first (as a little-endian uint32_t) followed by all elements using `write_container`.

4. **Metadata Serialization**: Used `hexi::null_terminated(metadata)` which writes the string data followed by a null terminator.

5. **Buffer Management**: Created a `buffer_adaptor` for `std::vector<uint8_t>` and used it to construct a `binary_stream`, then called the packet's `serialise` method.

The implementation follows the exact specifications provided, using the appropriate Hexi library functions and adaptors as documented in the reference materials.

